    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-03-03T21:13:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-03-03T21:13:00-05:00" n="734"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d734">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861a.01/204: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Vladivostok</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Macgowan</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Vladivostok</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-03-04T11:00:00+08:47">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 4, 1922—11 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received March 4—8:33 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>12. Embassy informed. Spiridon Merculoff has resigned as President of the
                    Provisional Government. Successor is Yeremeiff, Mayor of Vladivostok.<note
                        n="70" xml:id="d734fn70">After a few days the <hi rend="italic">status
                            quo</hi> under Merkulov was restored.</note> Immediate cause was the
                    growing dissatisfaction <pb facs="0962" n="848" xml:id="pg_848"/> with the
                    President’s dictatorial ways though total bankruptcy of the Government and the
                    retreat of the Army contributed. Failure of the Army is due to lack of funds and
                    ammunition and excessive losses from frostbite.</p>
                <p>Situation unstable and there is talk about military dictatorship under General
                        Verschbitsky,<note n="71" xml:id="d734fn71">Leader of the Kappel
                        troops.</note> commanding the Army. Japanese authorities watchful and
                    doubtless they will shape the final result.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Macgowan</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
